= f.fieldset("Enter a Unique Code", condition_opts(condition)) do
  = f.hidden_field(:type)
  = f.input(:active, :as => :boolean, :first_inline => true)
  = f.input(:limit, :class => 'tiny', :inline => true)
  = f.input(:code_prefix, :class => 'small', :inline => true)
  = f.input(:code_suffix, :class => 'small', :inline => true)
  %div.help
    %p.summary
      Customers will be prompted to enter code on checkout

    %div.extra.islay-toggle
      %p
        Individual codes are generated up to the specified limit e.g. a limit
        of 50 will result in 50 unique codes. A prefix and/or suffix can be 
        provided. This can help identify which promotion a code applies to.
        A suffix like 'WAT' would generate a code like 'WATHG86D'.

        These codes are private; they are not advertised in the webshop. 
        Instead the codes will be listed in the promotion summary, where you 
        can then provide them to customers.

